# Repo-root .dockerignore — LEGACY-BUILDER FALLBACK NET.
#
# Modern Docker (BuildKit / `# syntax=` / Fly's remote builder) reads the
# adjacent `<dockerfile>.dockerignore` (e.g. examples/live-capstone/Dockerfile.dockerignore,
# benchmarks/Dockerfile.dockerignore) and IGNORES this root file for those images.
# The real deploy paths all force BuildKit, so this file does NOT change their behavior.
#
# This file exists only for the LEGACY builder (DOCKER_BUILDKIT=0 / an old engine),
# which skips per-Dockerfile ignores entirely. Without it, a legacy `COPY . .` would
# upload the ENTIRE monorepo — root node_modules, full .git history, var/ — into the
# build context and into the image.
#
# It also tightens the repo-root framework Dockerfile's `COPY . .` under any builder:
# that image brings its OWN production node_modules from the `deps` stage via
# `COPY --from=deps`, so a local node_modules must never overwrite it.
#
# Keep this CONSERVATIVE: only VCS metadata, dependency installs, build outputs, and
# local tooling caches / binary noise. Never exclude application SOURCE — both
# `COPY . .` images ship app + workspace source (*.ts, lesto.app.ts, package.json,
# migrations, static assets, packages/, examples/, site/, www/, docs/).

# Dependency installs (runtime images bring their own via `COPY --from=deps`)
node_modules
**/node_modules

# Version control
.git
.gitignore

# Local runtime scratch / sandbox-redirected writes
var

# Test + build outputs
coverage
**/coverage
dist
**/dist
build
**/build
.next
**/.next
.svelte-kit
**/.svelte-kit

# Local tooling caches / agent scratch
.claude
.playwright-mcp
.devcontainer

# Large binary noise (screenshots, etc.)
*.png
